00:12:38,178 --> 00:12:42,014
<i>[ Bell Continues Ringing ]</i>

169
00:13:08,141 --> 00:13:12,978
<i>Please, God, don't let me</i>
<i>fall in love and want to do</i>
<i>disgusting things.</i>

170
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:23,623
<i>Dear God,</i>
<i>I love the way he throws.</i>

171
00:13:25,659 --> 00:13:28,827
[ Gasping ]

172
00:13:34,100 --> 00:13:36,402
<i> [ Typing Continues ]</i>

173
00:13:38,004 --> 00:13:40,005
[ Muffled ]
Come on.

174
00:13:43,677 --> 00:13:45,844
Mrs. Flax...

175
00:13:45,912 --> 00:13:48,247
<i> I'm taking my fiancee</i>
<i> out to lunch.</i>

176
00:13:48,314 --> 00:13:50,616
I expect you to be here
when I return.

177
00:13:50,684 --> 00:13:52,785
<i>Hi, sweetie.</i>

178
00:13:52,852 --> 00:13:55,621
How are
those depositions coming?

179
00:13:55,689 --> 00:13:57,690
They'll be ready.

180
00:14:01,295 --> 00:14:03,629
Assholes.

181
00:14:04,631 --> 00:14:08,534
<i>♪ Big girls don't cry ♪</i>

182
00:14:08,602 --> 00:14:11,804
<i>♪ Big girls don't cry ♪♪</i>

183
00:14:15,141 --> 00:14:19,077
- Do you like your new boss, Mom?
- No, sweetheart, I don't.

184
00:14:19,145 --> 00:14:21,246
- You make out the list?
- Yeah. Kate needs a new swimsuit.

185
00:14:21,315 --> 00:14:23,248
I need notebooks, pens
and underwear.

186
00:14:23,317 --> 00:14:26,419
I only have a half an hour for lunch,
so after we pick out the shoes,

187
00:14:26,486 --> 00:14:28,587
- Then I'll give you money and you can buy the rest.
- Okay.

188
00:14:28,655 --> 00:14:30,589
- I want red ones.
- All right.

189
00:14:30,657 --> 00:14:33,926
- Bright red ones with a red strap.
- Yes, Katie.

190
00:14:33,993 --> 00:14:37,262
- I don't need any.
- Charlotte, don't aggravate me.

191
00:14:37,331 --> 00:14:39,932
You're starting a new school on monday
and those boots aren't.

192
00:14:39,999 --> 00:14:42,267
- What's wrong with them?
- Everything!

193
00:14:42,336 --> 00:14:44,537
[ Scoffs ]

194
00:14:45,672 --> 00:14:47,606
<i>[ Baseball Announcer, Indistinct ]</i>

195
00:14:47,674 --> 00:14:50,275
Because I'm the best mother in the world.

196
00:14:50,343 --> 00:14:52,478
<i>[ Door Bell Rings ]</i>
I'll be right with you.

197
00:14:52,546 --> 00:14:55,047
<i>[ Charlotte ]</i>
<i>Hail Mary, full of grace.</i>

198
00:14:55,114 --> 00:14:57,282
<i>[ Baseball Announcer Continues ]</i>

199
00:14:57,350 --> 00:15:00,085
<i> [ Mrs. Flax ] - Katydid.</i>
<i>[ Kate ] - Let me try them on.</i>

200
00:15:05,925 --> 00:15:07,926
You must be Mrs. Flax.

201
00:15:07,994 --> 00:15:12,631
<i>Joseph told us that a nice
Jewish family were our new neighbors.</i>

202
00:15:12,699 --> 00:15:14,967
Welcome to East Port.

203
00:15:15,034 --> 00:15:17,370
<i>[ Charlotte ]</i>
<i>Oh, God, please let Mrs. Flax</i>
<i>control herself.</i>

204
